    "locked": false,
    "maintainer_can_modify": true,
    "title": "test: add coverage for cmpctblock revert-to-header processing",
    "user": {
      "login": "shuv-amp",
      "id": 63120087,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjYzMTIwMDg3",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/63120087?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/shuv-amp",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/shuv-amp",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/shuv-amp/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/shuv-amp/following%7B/other_user%7D",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/shuv-amp/gists%7B/gist_id%7D",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/shuv-amp/starred%7B/owner%7D%7B/repo%7D",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/shuv-amp/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/shuv-amp/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/shuv-amp/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/shuv-amp/events%7B/privacy%7D",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/shuv-amp/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false,
      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "When a `CMPCTBLOCK` is received for a block more than two heights above the\r\nactive chain tip, and the block was not requested from the sending peer,\r\n`net_processing` sets `fRevertToHeaderProcessing` and routes the header through\r\n`ProcessHeadersMessage()`. That fallback is currently untested.\r\n\r\nAs noted in #34618, the `fRevertToHeaderProcessing` declaration, assignment,\r\nand check can currently be removed without any test failures.\r\n\r\nThis PR adds `test_cmpctblock_revert_to_header_processing` to\r\n`test/functional/p2p_compactblocks.py`. The test:\r\n\r\n1. Builds three blocks extending the active tip.\r\n2. Sends `HEADERS` for the first two blocks so the node learns the\r\n   intermediate headers.\r\n3. Sends a `CMPCTBLOCK` for the third block, which is more than two heights\r\n   above the active tip and was not requested from that peer.\r\n4. Verifies the node issues a follow-up `getdata` request for the block,\r\n   consistent with the header-processing fallback.\r\n5. Verifies the active chain tip does not advance.\r\n\r\nCloses #34618",
