      "message": "test: add coverage for cmpctblock revert-to-header path\n\nWhen a peer sends an unsolicited cmpctblock for a block more than two\nheights ahead of the active tip, net_processing sets\nfRevertToHeaderProcessing and hands the header to\nProcessHeadersMessage(). That path is currently untested.\n\nAdd a functional test that builds a three-block extension of the active\ntip, announces the first two blocks by header, and then sends the third\nas a cmpctblock. This exercises the far-ahead fallback and verifies\nthat the node keeps the active tip unchanged and issues a follow-up\ngetdata request for the announced block.\n\nCloses #34618",
      "committer": {
        "name": "Shuvam Pandey",
        "email": "shuvampandey1@gmail.com",
        "date": "2026-03-03T17:32:34Z"
      },
